im$ 20 to 30 times less costly\nregarding the training phase than the traditional shallow FNNs, thus arising as\na promising alternative to deep learning for solving the inverse problem for\nhigh-dimensional PDEs.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 31 Jan 2022 16:21:31 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 15 Feb 2022 08:59:42 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-03-16"}
