, in general observations of IRAS08 find the most\ntension with theories in which star formation efficiency is a constant. Our\nresults argue for the need of high spatial resolution CO observations are a\nlarger number of similar targets.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 31 Jan 2022 19:00:04 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-04-13"}
