 modified gravity parameters. If GR is the correct theory of gravity, and\nassuming narrow priors on the cosmological parameters, we forecast an\nuncertainty of the modified gravity parameter $\\Xi_0$ of 51% with $\\sim 90$\ndetections at O4-like sensitivities, and $\\Xi_0$ of 20% with an additional\n$\\sim 400$ detections at O5-like sensitivity. We also consider how these\nforecasts depend on the current uncertainties of the BBH population.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 31 Jan 2022 19:00:05 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 12 Jul 2022 12:13:39 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-09-15"}
